 single interpretative frame and a novel approach to border crossing: an analysis of the reconfiguration of memory, personal and group time that follows the migrants' renegotiation of cross-border space and recalibrations of temporality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aborder crossing.  amigrant networks.  apost-Soviet transition.  atemporality.1 aCassidy, Kathryn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDonnan, Hastings, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDonnan, Hastings, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGregorič Bon, Nataša, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarper, Robin A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHurd, Madeleine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHurd, Madeleine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKovras, Iosif, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKramsch, Olivier Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeutloff-Grandits, Carolin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeutloff-Grandits, Carolin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLofranco, Zaira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobins, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTošić, Jelena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZubida, Hani, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dD